  <brief_title>Disability, Perceived Social Support and Quality of Life in Multiple Sclerosis</brief_title>
  <acronym>QUALVIE-SEP</acronym>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Fondation Ophtalmologique Adolphe de Rothschild</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Fondation Ophtalmologique Adolphe de Rothschild</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The World Health Organization International Classification of Functioning, Disability and
      Health has shown that the environment can play a major role in patients' disability, and
      hence in their quality of life. This study considers social dimensions of quality of life,
      particularly family as well as social and professional networks.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
